metadata.name: Protein Pelt #508
metadata.description:
An incorrectly placed decimal point led to this pattern. A good friend told me it reminded them of protein structures, I found them to look like animal pelts strewn about.

Each "protein" is made up of 100 pelts, random walking around the canvas from the center. Each "pelt" is made of 5 colors sampled from an array of 84 colors.

Press 's' when in live view to save the image.

metadata.name: Chaotic Boards #8
metadata.description:
Emotional art always interests me. And for emotionality you need to add a little chaos to the artwork. In mathematical terms, the tangent is that bad guy who does it all the time.

This is a continuation of the series "Math Shapes". Here, too, one board is described by one mathematical function.

Press the key: 
	- "s" to save the image at current resolution,
	- "2" to save the big image at 2000x2000px resolution, 
	- "4" to save the big image at 4000x4000px resolution.

12.2021.

metadata.name: Pipe Dream #99
metadata.description:
The term "pipe dream" typically refers to an unrealistic or unattainable dream.

The series explores elusive ambitions. Artists are frequently cautioned that their journey may be seen as a mere pipe dream, a path filled with challenges, setbacks, and uncertainties. Society often questions the practicality of pursuing one's passions.

Each iteration serves as a reminder of your potential, any goal can transcend skepticism and the perception of impossibility, no matter how tough or unlikely it seems.

Made with p5js in aijs.

metadata.name: Orbit Traps #123
metadata.description:
This is my first foray into generative NFTs. This is a variation of the Mandelbrot set. I first built a tool in Unity to find and record interesting locations of the set. Then I real-time render these parts inside of a shader and apply different orbit traps to the fractal. There is quite a bit of variation. Apart from different parts, and zoom levels, of the set, there are different orbit traps, symmetries, colors and animations (rare). I tried to balance the variety of images with the visual quality. This is a trade off because the more variety you allow for, the more likely it is that some of them will not look ideal. 

In the unlikely event you mint a completely black or white image, drop me a mail at countfrolic@gmail.com and I'll gladly mint you a new one.

Yours,
Martijn Steinrucken
The Art of Code

metadata.name: Neon Painter #3
metadata.description:
The Neon Painter / 2021

The Idea of Painter series got started when I received an artwork, oil painted canvas that my distant relative had painted and fell in love with it. From since I have been dreaming of a algorithm that generates similar art to canvas.

The Neon Painter is first step towards fulfilling my dream. This Painter was inspired by Chris Randall's work here at fxhash. Hopefully You will enjoy my Painters as much as I do enjoy making them.

Made with P5JS and neons.

metadata.name: Creta Sarculum #145
metadata.description:
An exploration of simple chalk rake designs. 

Each piece has a few key variables, probabilities for those variables are as follows:

75% Gradient Background
25% Solid Color Background
4.76% Each Chalk Color Palette (21 palettes)
50% Circular Modifier
25% Rectangular Modifier
15% Rectangular Gradient Modifier

Press 's' in Live View to save a full resolution image.

metadata.name: Multi-Biome #14
metadata.description:
Inspired by Jose Margulis's "Alpine Landscape"

Designed to be viewed as if you're walking past on the gallery wall, Multi-Biome is an interative play on perspective and scale. Each landscape is created from between 50 and 200 planes, slicing the landscape along a single axis.

Click and drag to rotate.

Press "s" in live view to save a png.

metadata.name: Unknown Monuments #7
metadata.description:
That Monument belongs to someone.

.Four seasons of the year.
.Three Forest Densities.
.Nine monuments.
.Can be actived or inactive.
.Rare raining.

-

Monuments often seem peaceful,
Perhaps they bring mute regrets,
Maybe bloody words and gestures,
Perhaps even peace itself!

They are always rich and full of glory.
They always cry out to the history of a people

One of these days I'll build a monument.
Not a monument for what's great.
But a monumento for the misunderstood.
A monument of clay and blood.
A monument of old newspaper pieces,
A monument of bones and gold,
A monument covered in autumn leaves,
A damp monument,

Because it brings tears.

-

by Gen Doodler | twitter.com/GenDoodler
